Package: mint-mechanic
Version: 0.6.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Ron Craig (rclinux) <rcraig.netmail@gmail.com>
Installed-Size: 170
Depends: gir1.2-gtk-4.0, libgtk-4-1, pkexec, python3, python3-gi, python3-psutil
Recommends: deborphan
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/rclinux/mint-mechanic
Description: maintained tune-up tool for Linux Mint
 A modern, Cinnamon-native successor to Stacer: a live system dashboard with
 animated CPU / RAM / Disk gauges plus a GPU dial, married to the action
 features Mint does not ship (services, cleaner, startup manager, uninstaller)
 and a package-profile export tied to disaster recovery.
 .
 Mint Mechanic never runs as root. Reads run as the user and each mutating
 action elevates on its own via polkit (pkexec). Anything that removes packages
 shows APT's real removal cascade, requires confirmation, and refuses outright
 when the removal would take the desktop, login manager or graphics driver.
